To create EKS cluster using eksctl

$ eksctl create cluster \
> --name demo-cluster \
> --version 1.21 \
> --region us-east-1 \
> --nodegroup-name demo-eks-nodes \
> --node-type t2.micro \
> --nodes 2

To delete EKS cluster using eksctl
$ eksctl delete cluster \
> --region=us-east-1 \
> --name=demo-cluster

